<h1>The Framework</h1>

<p>The named parts of the practice, rendered as the documents that define them. The
narrative spine is the <strong>Kamae chain</strong>—five documents that carry a project
from opinions to a working session, each step narrowing what is possible. It is the
obviously-right order, never a locked door.</p>

<figure class="chain-figure">
  <div class="chain-scales">
    <div><div class="chain-scale-label">full ≥480px</div>{% chainSvg "full" %}</div>
    <div><div class="chain-scale-label">header ≥160px</div>{% chainSvg "header" %}</div>
    <div><div class="chain-scale-label">glyph &lt;160px</div>{% chainSvg "glyph" %}</div>
  </div>
  <figcaption class="caption">One SVG source, three scales by reduction (§6). Kamae 1–4 in
  bero (thinking), Kamae 5 in sumi (doing); the crossing arrow prints kachi. The koma marks
  only where work is steppable. Gold never appears here—the chain is structure, not state.</figcaption>
</figure>

